data.content:
Here's the output:

```json
{
  "Name": "Alice",
  "Age": 30
}
```

And the full program (`Program.cs` targeting `net11.0`):

```csharp
using System;
using System.Text.Json;

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase,
    WriteIndented = true
};

var person = new Person("Alice", 30);
Console.WriteLine(JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, options));

public record Person(string name, int age);
```

The key is `JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase` — a built-in policy added in .NET 9. It converts the record's constructor parameter names (`name`, `age`) to PascalCase (`Name`, `Age`) in the serialized JSON.
